# CSV Parser Library

A robust, feature-rich TypeScript CSV parser with comprehensive support for quoted fields, custom delimiters, automatic type coercion, and powerful aggregation methods.

## Features

вњ… **Basic CSV Parsing** - Parse CSV strings into arrays of objects with automatic header detection  
вњ… **Quoted Fields** - Handle fields wrapped in double quotes, including fields containing delimiters  
вњ… **Escaped Quotes** - Support for escaped quotes within quoted fields (RFC 4180 compliant)  
вњ… **Custom Delimiters** - Configure delimiter, quote character, and line separator  
вњ… **Automatic Type Coercion** - Detect and convert numbers, booleans, and null values  
вњ… **Error Handling** - Collect parsing errors without crashing; continue processing valid rows  
вњ… **Chainable Filtering** - Filter rows with predicates and chain multiple filters  
вњ… **Aggregation Methods** - Sum, average, count, and groupBy operations on parsed data  

## Installation

```bash
npm install csv-parser-lib
```

Or use the TypeScript source directly:

```typescript
import { parseCSV, CSVOptions, CSVResult } from './csv-parser';
```

## Quick Start

```typescript
import { parseCSV } from './csv-parser';

const csv = `name,age,email
John,30,john@example.com
Jane,25,jane@example.com`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows);
// [
//   { name: 'John', age: 30, email: 'john@example.com' },
//   { name: 'Jane', age: 25, email: 'jane@example.com' }
// ]

console.log(result.headers);
// ['name', 'age', 'email']

console.log(result.errors);
// []
```

## API Reference

### `parseCSV(input: string, options?: CSVOptions): CSVResult`

Parse a CSV string into structured data.

#### Parameters

- **input** (string): The CSV string to parse
- **options** (CSVOptions, optional): Configuration object

#### CSVOptions

```typescript
interface CSVOptions {
  delimiter?: string;        // Field delimiter (default: ',')
  quote?: string;            // Quote character (default: '"')
  lineSeparator?: string;    // Line separator (default: '\n')
  typeCoercion?: boolean;    // Enable type coercion (default: true)
}
```

#### Returns

A `CSVResult` object with the following structure:

```typescript
interface CSVResult {
  rows: Record<string, any>[];
  headers: string[];
  errors: ParseError[];
  filter(predicate: (row, index) => boolean): CSVResult;
  sum(column: string): number;
  average(column: string): number;
  count(): number;
  groupBy(column: string): Map<any, Record<string, any>[]>;
}
```

## Usage Examples

### Basic Parsing

```typescript
const csv = `id,name,status
1,Alice,active
2,Bob,inactive
3,Carol,active`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);
console.log(result.rows);
// [
//   { id: 1, name: 'Alice', status: 'active' },
//   { id: 2, name: 'Bob', status: 'inactive' },
//   { id: 3, name: 'Carol', status: 'active' }
// ]
```

### Quoted Fields with Commas

```typescript
const csv = `name,description,price
"Smith, John","A product with, commas",19.99
"Doe, Jane","Another item, really great",29.99`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);
console.log(result.rows[0]);
// {
//   name: 'Smith, John',
//   description: 'A product with, commas',
//   price: 19.99
// }
```

### Escaped Quotes

```typescript
const csv = `name,quote
"John ""The King"" Doe","He said ""Hello"""`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);
console.log(result.rows[0]);
// {
//   name: 'John "The King" Doe',
//   quote: 'He said "Hello"'
// }
```

### Custom Delimiters

```typescript
// Using semicolon as delimiter
const csv = `name;age;city
John;30;NYC
Jane;25;LA`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, { delimiter: ';' });
console.log(result.rows[0]);
// { name: 'John', age: 30, city: 'NYC' }

// Using single quotes
const csv2 = `name,description
'John Smith','A person with, commas'
'Jane Doe','Another person, here'`;

const result2 = parseCSV(csv2, { quote: "'" });
console.log(result2.rows[0]);
// { name: 'John Smith', description: 'A person with, commas' }

// Windows CRLF line endings
const csv3 = `name,age\r\nAlice,28\r\nBob,35`;
const result3 = parseCSV(csv3, { lineSeparator: '\r\n' });
```

### Type Coercion

The parser automatically converts values to appropriate types:

```typescript
const csv = `id,price,active,status
1,19.99,true,null
2,29.50,false,active
3,99.99,True,NULL`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);
console.log(result.rows[0]);
// {
//   id: 1,                    // number
//   price: 19.99,             // number (float)
//   active: true,             // boolean
//   status: null              // null
// }

// Disable type coercion
const result2 = parseCSV(csv, { typeCoercion: false });
console.log(result2.rows[0]);
// {
//   id: '1',
//   price: '19.99',
//   active: 'true',
//   status: 'null'
// }
```

### Error Handling

```typescript
const csv = `name,age
"John Doe,john@example.com
Jane,25
Bob,35`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows);
// [
//   { name: 'Jane', age: 25 },
//   { name: 'Bob', age: 35 }
// ]

console.log(result.errors);
// [
//   { row: 2, message: 'Unclosed quoted field' }
// ]
```

### Filtering

```typescript
const csv = `product,category,price,quantity
Laptop,Electronics,999.99,5
Mouse,Electronics,29.99,50
Desk,Furniture,299.99,3
Chair,Furniture,199.99,10`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Single filter
const electronics = result.filter(row => row.category === 'Electronics');
console.log(electronics.count());
// 2

// Chained filters
const affordableFurniture = result
  .filter(row => row.category === 'Furniture')
  .filter(row => row.price < 250);
console.log(affordableFurniture.rows);
// [{ product: 'Chair', category: 'Furniture', price: 199.99, quantity: 10 }]

// Filter with index
const evenRows = result.filter((row, index) => index % 2 === 0);
```

### Aggregation - Sum

```typescript
const csv = `product,price,quantity
Laptop,999.99,5
Mouse,29.99,50
Desk,299.99,3`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

const total = result.sum('price');
console.log(total);
// 1329.97

// Sum only filtered data
const desks = result.filter(row => row.product === 'Desk');
console.log(desks.sum('price'));
// 299.99
```

### Aggregation - Average

```typescript
const csv = `id,score
1,80
2,90
3,100`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

const avgScore = result.average('score');
console.log(avgScore);
// 90

// Average of filtered data
const highScores = result.filter(row => row.score >= 90);
console.log(highScores.average('score'));
// 95
```

### Aggregation - Count

```typescript
const csv = `id,name,status
1,John,active
2,Jane,inactive
3,Bob,active
4,Alice,active`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.count());
// 4

const active = result.filter(row => row.status === 'active');
console.log(active.count());
// 3
```

### Aggregation - GroupBy

```typescript
const csv = `name,department,salary
John,Engineering,80000
Jane,Sales,70000
Bob,Engineering,85000
Alice,Sales,72000`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

const byDept = result.groupBy('department');
console.log(byDept.size);
// 2

console.log(byDept.get('Engineering'));
// [
//   { name: 'John', department: 'Engineering', salary: 80000 },
//   { name: 'Bob', department: 'Engineering', salary: 85000 }
// ]

// Get average salary by department
for (const [dept, employees] of byDept) {
  const salaries = employees.reduce((sum, e) => sum + e.salary, 0);
  const avgSalary = salaries / employees.length;
  console.log(`${dept}: $${avgSalary.toFixed(2)}`);
}
// Engineering: $82500.00
// Sales: $71000.00

// GroupBy on filtered data
const seniorEngineers = result
  .filter(row => row.salary > 82000)
