# CSV Parser - Quick Reference Guide

## Installation & Import

```javascript
// JavaScript/Node.js
const { parseCSV } = require('./csv-parser');

// TypeScript
import { parseCSV, CSVOptions, CSVResult } from './csv-parser';
```

## Basic Usage

```javascript
const result = parseCSV(csvString);
console.log(result.headers);  // ['col1', 'col2', 'col3']
console.log(result.rows);     // [{ col1: ..., col2: ..., col3: ... }, ...]
console.log(result.errors);   // [{ row: 2, message: '...' }, ...]
```

## Options

```javascript
parseCSV(csv, {
  delimiter: ';',              // default: ','
  quote: "'",                  // default: '"'
  lineSeparator: '\r\n',       // default: '\n'
  typeCoercion: true           // default: true
});
```

## Methods

### filter(predicate)
```javascript
result.filter(row => row.age > 25)
result.filter((row, index) => index % 2 === 0)
```

### sum(column)
```javascript
result.sum('amount')                    // в†’ 1500
result.filter(...).sum('price')         // Sum on filtered data
```

### average(column)
```javascript
result.average('score')                 // в†’ 85.5
result.filter(...).average('price')     // Average on filtered data
```

### count()
```javascript
result.count()                          // в†’ 42
result.filter(...).count()              // Count filtered rows
```

### groupBy(column)
```javascript
const groups = result.groupBy('category');
for (const [category, rows] of groups) {
  console.log(category, rows.length);
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Filter and Count
```javascript
const active = result.filter(r => r.status === 'active');
console.log(active.count());  // Number of active items
```

### Filter and Sum
```javascript
const expensive = result.filter(r => r.price > 100);
const total = expensive.sum('price');
```

### Filter and Average
```javascript
const recent = result.filter(r => r.year >= 2020);
const avgPrice = recent.average('price');
```

### Multiple Filters
```javascript
result
  .filter(r => r.status === 'active')
  .filter(r => r.price < 50)
  .filter(r => r.quantity > 10)
```

### GroupBy and Iterate
```javascript
const byDept = result.groupBy('department');
for (const [dept, employees] of byDept) {
  const count = employees.length;
  const avgSalary = employees.reduce((s, e) => s + e.salary, 0) / count;
  console.log(`${dept}: ${count} employees, avg salary $${avgSalary}`);
}
```

## Type Coercion

| Input String | Output Type | Example |
|--------------|------------|---------|
| `"123"` | number | 123 |
| `"45.67"` | number | 45.67 |
| `"1e5"` | number | 100000 |
| `"-100"` | number | -100 |
| `"true"` | boolean | true |
| `"false"` | boolean | false |
| `"null"` | null | null |
| `""` | null | null |
| `"text"` | string | "text" |

**Disable with:**
```javascript
parseCSV(csv, { typeCoercion: false })
```

## Error Handling

```javascript
const result = parseCSV(csv);

if (result.errors.length > 0) {
  result.errors.forEach(error => {
    console.log(`Row ${error.row}: ${error.message}`);
  });
}

// Parser continues anyway - use valid rows
console.log(result.rows.length);  // Successfully parsed rows
```

## Special Cases

### Quoted Fields with Commas
```javascript
const csv = `name,description
"Smith, John","A product, great"`;
// result.rows[0].name в†’ "Smith, John"
```

### Escaped Quotes
```javascript
const csv = `name,quote
"John ""King"" Doe","He said ""Hi"""`;
// result.rows[0].name в†’ "John "King" Doe"
```

### Custom Delimiters
```javascript
// Semicolon
parseCSV('a;b;c\n1;2;3', { delimiter: ';' })

// Pipe
parseCSV('a|b|c\n1|2|3', { delimiter: '|' })

// Tab
parseCSV('a\tb\tc\n1\t2\t3', { delimiter: '\t' })
```

### Windows Line Endings
```javascript
parseCSV(csv, { lineSeparator: '\r\n' })
```

## Type Definitions

```typescript
interface CSVOptions {
  delimiter?: string;
  quote?: string;
  lineSeparator?: string;
  typeCoercion?: boolean;
}

interface CSVResult {
  rows: Record<string, any>[];
  headers: string[];
  errors: ParseError[];
  filter(predicate: (row: any, index: number) => boolean): CSVResult;
  sum(column: string): number;
  average(column: string): number;
  count(): number;
  groupBy(column: string): Map<any, Record<string, any>[]>;
}

interface ParseError {
  row: number;
  message: string;
}
```

## Real-World Examples

### Sales Analysis
```javascript
const data = parseCSV(salesCsv);

// Top performers
const topPerformers = data
  .filter(r => r.revenue > 50000)
  .groupBy('region');

// Average sales by region
for (const [region, sales] of topPerformers) {
  const avg = sales.reduce((sum, s) => sum + s.revenue, 0) / sales.length;
  console.log(`${region}: $${avg.toFixed(2)}`);
}
```

### Data Filtering
```javascript
const users = parseCSV(usersCsv);

// Active users
const active = users.filter(u => u.status === 'active');
console.log(`${active.count()} active users`);

// By country
const byCountry = active.groupBy('country');
console.log(`${byCountry.size} countries with active users`);
```

### Statistical Analysis
```javascript
const scores = parseCSV(scoresCsv);

const stats = {
  total: scores.count(),
  min: Math.min(...scores.rows.map(r => r.score)),
  max: Math.max(...scores.rows.map(r => r.score)),
  sum: scores.sum('score'),
  average: scores.average('score'),
  byGrade: scores.groupBy('grade')
};
```

## Error Messages

| Message | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Unclosed quoted field | Missing closing quote | Check quote balance |
| Expected N fields but got M | Row has wrong column count | Check delimiters in row |
| Failed to parse header line | Header line is malformed | Verify first row format |

## Performance Tips

1. **Large files:** Parser uses single-pass O(n) algorithm
2. **Many columns:** No performance issues up to 100+ columns
3. **Many rows:** Handles 1000+ rows efficiently
4. **Type coercion:** Disable if not needed with `typeCoercion: false`
5. **Filtering:** Chain filters for better readability, no performance penalty

## Browser Compatibility

- Modern browsers (ES2015+)
- Node.js 12+
- No external dependencies
- Works in CommonJS and ES6 modules

## Common Mistakes

### вќЊ Don't forget header row
```javascript
// WRONG - CSV must have headers
const result = parseCSV('John,30\nJane,25');

// CORRECT - First row becomes headers
const result = parseCSV('name,age\nJohn,30\nJane,25');
```

### вќЊ Don't forget quotes for comma-containing fields
```javascript
// WRONG - Comma will split the field
name,address
John,123 Main St, City

// CORRECT - Quote fields with commas
name,address
John,"123 Main St, City"
```

### вќЊ Don't forget type checking
```javascript
// WRONG - Forgetting type coercion
const result = parseCSV(csv);
result.rows[0].age + 10  // "30" + 10 = "3010"

// CORRECT - Type is coerced automatically
const result = parseCSV(csv);
result.rows[0].age + 10  // 30 + 10 = 40
```

### вќЊ Don't assume filter returns array
```javascript
// WRONG
const filtered = result.filter(r => r.active);
filtered[0]  // undefined!

// CORRECT - filter returns CSVResult
const filtered = result.filter(r => r.active);
filtered.rows[0]  // correct
```

## Summary

- **Parse:** `parseCSV(csv, options)`
- **Access:** `result.rows`, `result.headers`, `result.errors`
- **Filter:** `result.filter(predicate)`
- **Aggregate:** `result.sum()`, `result.average()`, `result.count()`, `result.groupBy()`
- **Chain:** All methods return CSVResult for chaining
- **Robust:** Continues parsing after errors

